content: No file will be copied. The original file will be retained in the destination folder.

comment.text: This translation key provides a message to be displayed when skipping file copy operations, indicating that the original file will remain in the destination folder. It appears in UI elements where users can choose to skip copying files, such as a conflict resolution dialog.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Heç bir fayl köçürülmədi. Orijinal fayl köçürülən yerdə dəyişikliksiz qaldı." doesn't fully capture the meaning of "No file will be copied. The original file will be retained in the destination folder." While 'Heç bir fayl köçürülmədi' is correct for 'No file will be copied,' 'Orijinal fayl köçürülən yerdə dəyişikliksiz qaldı' translates to 'The original file remained unchanged in the place it was copied to.' This is a bit confusing - it implies a prior copying action. The intended meaning is that it remains in the *destination* folder.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Heç bir fayl köçürülmədi. Orijinal fayl son məqsəd yerində olduğu kimi qaldı.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: There is an unnecessary space before the colon after "Ոչ մի ֆայլ չի պատճենվի".
The word 'ໂຟນເດີ້' seems to be a misspelling of 'ໂຟນເດີ'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ໄຟລ໌ຈະບໍ່ຖືກສຳເນົາ ໄຟລ໌ຕົ້ນສະບັບຈະຖືກເກັບໄວ້ໃນໂຟນເດີ.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Latvian translation 'Fails tiks pievienots failam ar tādu pašu nosaukumu kā versijai' does not accurately convey the meaning of 'No file will be copied. The original file will be retained in the destination folder.' It translates to something like 'A file will be added to the file with the same name as the version'. This implies a versioning process, which is not indicated in the English content.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A more accurate translation would be something along the lines of 'Atteiks fails. Oriģinālais fails tiks saglabāts galamērķa mapē.' (No file will be skipped. The original file will be retained in the destination folder.)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The verb tense 'o să fie' (will be) can sound slightly awkward in this context. While grammatically correct, a more natural phrasing would be 'va fi'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Niciun fișier nu va fi copiat. Fișierul de origine rămâne în dosarul de destinație.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'ගමනාන්ත' (gamanantha) is a formal term for 'destination'. While technically correct, a more common and accessible term might be preferred. Consider using 'නිෂ්පාදන ස්ථානය' (nispadana sthanaya) or a similar equivalent.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: කිසිදු ගොනුවක් පිටපත් නොකෙරේ. මුල් ගොනුව නිෂ්පාදන ස්ථානයේ රඳවා තැබෙනු ඇත.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'shranjena' (saved) isn't the most accurate translation of 'retained' in this context. 'Ohranjena' would be a better fit to convey the meaning of keeping the original file.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Nobena datoteka ne bo kopirana. Izvirna datoteka bo ohranjena v ciljni mapi.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'folder' is transliterated as 'фолдер'. The Serbian word for folder is 'папка'.
